{"title_page": "Steve Matteson", "text_new": "'''Steven R. Matteson''' (born 1965, [[Chicago, Illinois]]) is an American [[typeface]] designer whose work is included in several computer operating systems and embedded in game consoles, cell phones and other electronic devices.<ref name=\"Steve Matteson interview\">{{cite web|title=Steve Matteson interview|url=https://www.myfonts.com/newsletters/cc/201205.html|website=MyFonts|accessdate=8 April 2016}}</ref> He is the designer of the Microsoft font family [[Segoe UI|Segoe]] included since [[Windows XP]];<ref>{{cite web |url=http://itmanagement.earthweb.com/columns/executive_tech/article.php/3601421 |title=Designer Says Vista Font is Original |first=Brian |last=Livingston|date=25 April 2006 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070302120256/http://itmanagement.earthweb.com/columns/executive_tech/article.php/3601421 |archivedate=2007-03-02}}</ref> of the [[droid (font)|Droid]] font collection used in the [[Android (operating system)|Android]] mobile device platform,<ref>[http://www.ascendercorp.com/pr/pr2007_11_12.html Ascender creates the new Droid font collection for Open Handset Alliance's Android platform<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> and designed the brand and user-interface fonts used in both the original Microsoft [[Xbox (console)|Xbox]] and the [[Xbox 360]].<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20070829184241/http://www.desktopmag.com.au/news_articles.php?article_id=24&type=Featured%20Articles&period=200704 Desktop - Australian Design, Digital Culture, Melbourne, Australia<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>\n\n==Biography==\nMatteson is a 1988 graduate of [[Rochester Institute of Technology]] where he studied [[typography]], [[design]] and printing. Upon graduation he spent two years learning [[font hinting]] technology while employed at laser-printer manufacturer QMS.\n\nIn 1990 Matteson began work at [[Monotype Corporation]] (later Agfa-Monotype) contributing to the creation of the [[Windows 3.1x]] core [[TrueType]] fonts: [[Arial]], [[Times New Roman]] and [[Courier New]].<ref>[http://www.myfonts.com/person/matteson/steve/ Steve Matteson : MyFonts<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>\n\nMatteson produced fonts for the Agfa-Monotype library (such as [[Goudy Ornate]] and [[Gill Floriated Capitals]]) and directed custom-font design for companies including [[Agilent Technologies]],<ref>[http://www.ascendercorp.com/portfolio_custom.html#Agilent Ascender Portfolio - Custom Fonts<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> [[NortonLifeLock|Symantec]] and [[Microsoft]].<ref>[http://www.ascendercorp.com/portfolio_custom.html#MS_Corp Ascender Portfolio - Custom Fonts<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> Matteson designed [[Andal\u00e9 Mono]] as a mono-spaced command line and coding font for [[Taligent]]. The font is now bundled with [[Mac OS X]] and was one of the original [[Core fonts for the Web]].\n\nMatteson directed custom type development for Agfa-Monotype until 2003. In 2004 he became a founding partner and Director of Type Design at [[Ascender Corporation]] in [[Elk Grove Village]], Illinois.<ref>[http://www.ascendercorp.com/stevepage.html Steve Matteson<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>\n\nIn 2005 Matteson designed the font family Convection for use in the branding and user-interface of Microsoft\u2019s [[Xbox 360]] game console. Matteson also designed the user-interface font used in Microsoft\u2019s [[Zune]] music player.<ref>[http://www.ascendercorp.com/portfolio_custom.html#Zune Ascender Portfolio - Custom Fonts<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> In 2007 software maker [[Red Hat]] released the open-source [[Liberation fonts]] family designed by Matteson.<ref>[https://www.redhat.com/promo/fonts/ redhat.com |<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> Also in 2007, Matteson designed the [[Droid (font)|Droid]] family of fonts included in the [[Android (operating system)|Android]] mobile-phone platform supported by the [[Open Handset Alliance]].\n\n==Fonts designed by Steve Matteson==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-4}}\n*[[Andal\u00e9 Mono]]\n*[[Andal\u00e9 Sans]]\n*Andy Bold\n*[[Croscore fonts|Arimo]]\n*Ascender Sans\n*Ascender Sans Bold\n*Ascender Serif\n*Ascender Serif Bold\n*Ayita\n*Ayita Bold\n*Binner Gothic\n*Blueprint\n*[[Cambria (typeface)|Cambria]]\n*[[Cambria (typeface)|Cambria Bold]]\n*Chicory\n*Convection\n{{col-4}}\n*[[Croscore fonts|Cousine]]\n*[[Curlz]]\n*Dujour\n*[[Droid (font)|Droid]]\n*Endurance Pro\n*Endurance Pro Black\n*Endurance Pro Light\n*Facade Condensed\n*Fineprint\n*Fineprint Swash One\n*Fineprint Swash Two\n*Goudy Ornate\n*Kootenay Pro\n*[[Liberation fonts|Liberation Mono]]\n*[[Liberation fonts|Liberation Sans]]\n{{col-4}}\n*[[Liberation fonts|Liberation Serif]]\n*Lindsey Pro\n*Massif Pro\n*Mayberry\n*Miramonte Pro\n*Miramonte Pro Bold\n*[[Noto fonts|Noto Sans for Latin]]<ref name=\"Noto FAQ\">{{cite web|title=Noto FAQ|url=https://www.google.com/get/noto/help/faq/|website=Google Noto Fonts|accessdate=29 September 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Open Sans]]\n*[[Open Sans|Open Sans Condensed]]\n*Open Serif\n*Othello\n*Pescadero Pro\n*Pescadero Pro Bold\n*[[Segoe]]\n*Sports Three\n*Sports Two\n*[[Croscore fonts|Tinos]]\n{{col-4}}\n*Titanium\n*Truesdell\n*Truesdell Ornaments\n*Twentieth Century Poster Fonts\n{{col-end}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Matteson, Steve}}\n[[Category:1965 births]]\n[[Category:Rochester Institute of Technology alumni]]\n[[Category:American typographers]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "text_old": "'''Steven R. Matteson''' (born 1965, [[Chicago, Illinois]]) is an American [[typeface]] designer whose work is included in several computer operating systems and embedded in game consoles, cell phones and other electronic devices.<ref name=\"Steve Matteson interview\">{{cite web|title=Steve Matteson interview|url=https://www.myfonts.com/newsletters/cc/201205.html|website=MyFonts|accessdate=8 April 2016}}</ref> He is the designer of the Microsoft font family [[Segoe UI|Segoe]] includ